\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "bib:arcsk2017"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 In applications such as crowd-sourcing and drug-designing, identifying
 a single good solution is often not sufficient.
 Moreover, finding the best subset might be hard due to the presence of
 many indistinguishably close solutions.
 Our generalisation of identifying exactly 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 arms out of the best 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $1\leq k\leq m$
\end_inset

, serves as a more effective alternative.
 We present a lower bound on the worst-case sample complexity for general
 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

, and a fully sequential PAC algorithm, 
