, which is more sample-efficient on easy instances.
 Also, extending our analysis to infinite-armed bandits, we present a PAC
 algorithm that is independent of 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

, which identifies an arm from the best 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

 fraction of arms using at most an additive poly-log number of samples than
 compared to the lower bound, thereby improving over
